This indicator is designed to identify high-probability breakout and breakdown opportunities by combining trendline structure with EMA trend filtering. The goal is to trade only in the direction of the dominant market trend while avoiding low-quality counter-trend setups.

How the Strategy Works
1. Trend Identification
The indicator uses the 200 EMA (Exponential Moving Average) to determine the overall market trend.
• Price above 200 EMA → Bullish trend
• Price below 200 EMA → Bearish trend
2. Trendline Detection
The script automatically identifies short-term trendlines based on recent price swings. These trendlines help detect potential momentum shifts and breakout zones.
3. Trade Signals
Signals are generated when price breaks a valid trendline in the direction of the main trend.
Buy Setup
• Price is above the 200 EMA
• A downward trendline is broken
• Candle closes above the trendline
Sell Setup
• Price is below the 200 EMA
• An upward trendline is broken
• Candle closes below the trendline
4. Risk Management
The indicator visually plots:
• Entry level
• Stop Loss
• Take Profit zone
This helps traders maintain clear risk-to-reward structures and avoid emotional decision making.

Best Timeframes

This strategy works best on intraday timeframes, especially:
• 1 minute
• 3 minute
• 5 minute
• 15 minute

It can be applied to crypto, forex, indices, and commodities.
